Saidi Balogun and Ayo Balogun are two of the film stars that have featured in AK Media’s new series, ‘Extra Mile.’ Directed by Tunde Olaoye, Extra mile also features Norbert Young, Vivian Anani, and Babaseun Faseru.   Why my new song Nigeria’ is special, by Uzoma Day     Why I want to empower women, by Doris Nkumah     Razzy AG hints at collaboration with top music acts   Speaking on the new series, the executive producer, Yosola Akindeju said, “We are here again to entertain people in Nigeria and beyond as we launch a new drama series that will be of great value to all. The new masterpiece is a family series that is laced with an entertaining storyline, romance, intrigues, guilt, trust, comic relief, and what have you. It is a basket with varieties, touching all spheres of human lives.” The new series is coming after the death of AK Media boss, Benson Akindeju. The content production company has family series that include Family ties, Face2Face, and Liberty Villa, in its repertoire.